Key Match Events: Travis Head scored 62 off 48 balls and took 2 wickets for 21 runs.
Mitchell Starc took 3 wickets for 34 runs.
Pat Cummins took 3 wickets for 51 runs.
Josh Hazlewood took 2 wickets for 12 runs.
Australia won by 3 wickets with 16 balls remaining.
Pre-Game Insights: South Africa won the toss and elected to bat first.
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Head was named Player of the Match.
Australia advanced to the final of the ICC Cricket World Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Eden Gardens, Kolkata.
The match was a day-night 50-over game.
